cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of detecting partially occluded objects, specifically faces. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves a novel loss layer for CNNs, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the error rate, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on public face detection benchmarks, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
